  "text": "First, by using a self-report scale such as the MDQ, we were dependent on the individuals' accuracy in reporting their bipolar symptoms. Furthermore, in a larger cohort that extended our sample from 20 to 92 bipolar phenotype individuals, the positive predictive value of the MDQ for bipolar disorder when used with the current screening criteria was relatively low at 40% [CITATION_1] .",
